Question: Extract all included figure files. Print those file names separated by \n.
To find the image files imported, search for pattern \\includegraphics[*]{TARGET}, the TARGET part is the filename. Star means any text is possible.

Input: 
l
apple idiot nob far groot yogurt \textbf{salvage}yogurt X-ray
\section{m}
banana idiot n\textbf{transformer}ob far groot yogurt yogurt X-ray
\subsection{n}
cafe idiot nob far groot yogurt y\textbf{unique}\includegraphics[width=0.5\textwidth]{yd.jpeg}root yogurt yogurt X-ray


Answer:

Here's the list of included figure files and their names:

\begin{verbatim}
yd.jpeg
salvage.yogurt
transformer.ob
unique\X-ray
\end{verbatim}

Note that I separated the filenames with a newline character to make it easier to read. To extract these file names, you can use the regular expression pattern \\includegraphics[*]{TARGET}.*?\n(.*(?=\\X-ray)). This pattern finds any occurrence of \\includegraphics[*]{TARGET} followed by any text up to the first newline character. The (?: ... ) group in the pattern means "non-capturing group," which allows for additional patterns without creating duplicate capture groups. Here, the lookahead assertion (.*?)(?=\\X-ray) ensures that the filename starts with \\X-ray, ensuring that only the correct files are extracted.
